# Me Too! — Find Your People

Me Too! is a frontend-only web application that helps users connect based on shared interests, hobbies, and location rather than appearance.

---

## Overview

This project demonstrates a simple social discovery platform built entirely with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It allows users to browse profiles, filter connections, and interact through a clean, responsive interface.

---

## Features

* User discovery with profile cards
* Search and filtering by location and gender
* Profile preview via modal
* Local login and signup using browser storage
* Friend request system (demo, non-persistent)
* Event discovery (static demo data)
* Responsive layout with modern UI design

---

## Project Structure

```
MeToo/
│
├── index.html
├── styles.css
├── script.js
└── README.md
```

---

## How It Works

### User Data

User profiles are fetched from the Random User API and enhanced with generated interests and bios.

### Authentication

Authentication is handled locally using `localStorage`. No real user verification is implemented.

### Friend Requests

Friend requests are stored temporarily in memory and are cleared when the page reloads.

### Search

Users can filter profiles based on:

* Location (text input)
* Gender selection

---

## Technologies

* HTML5
* CSS3
* Vanilla JavaScript (ES6)
* Random User API
* Google Fonts

---

## Limitations

* No backend or server
* No database integration
* No persistent data storage
* Authentication is not secure
* Friend requests are not saved

---

## Future Improvements

* Backend integration (Node.js / Express)
* Database support (MongoDB or PostgreSQL)
* Persistent user accounts
* Real-time messaging
* Profile editing functionality
* Notifications system

---

## Getting Started

1. Clone or download the project
2. Open `index.html` in your browser

```
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd MeToo
```

